# 🎸 Guitar Alchemist Research Playground

Welcome to the efficiency-tuned research environment for Guitar Alchemist.
This notebook is configured to load the domain projects directly, allowing for rapid experimentation and visualization.

## 🚀 Getting Started

The first cell loads the necessary projects and extensions. By using `#r "project:..."`, we ensure that any changes you make to the core library are immediately available here after a build.

#!csharp

// Load core projects
#r "project:../Common/GA.Core/GA.Core.csproj"
#r "project:../Common/GA.Domain.Core/GA.Domain.Core.csproj"
#r "project:../Common/GA.Domain.Services/GA.Domain.Services.csproj"
#r "project:../Common/GA.Business.Core/GA.Business.Core.csproj"
#r "project:../Common/GA.InteractiveExtension/GA.InteractiveExtension.csproj"

using GA.Domain.Core.Primitives.Notes;
using GA.Business.Core.Tonal;
using GA.InteractiveExtension.ExtensionMethods;
using GA.InteractiveExtension.KernelExtensions;

// Initialize GA Interactive Extensions
await kernel.UseGaAsync();

#!markdown

## 🎵 Music Theory Exploration

You can now use the domain objects directly. Use `.DisplayTable()` to view collections in a searchable grid.

#!csharp

using GA.Business.Core.Tonal.Modes;

// List all Melodic Minor modes
MelodicMinorMode.Objects.DisplayTable();

#!csharp

// Explore Keys
Key.Major.MajorItems.DisplayTable();

#!markdown

